# Context Data Legend (Optimized JSON)
The context data uses short keys to save tokens. Please use this mapping:
- **c**: Root Context
  - **m**: Manifest (Targets & Maps)
    - **t**: Targets (Files of interest)
      - **p**: path, **r**: reason, **c**: confidence (h=high, m=medium, l=low), **e**: evidence
    - **rm**: Repo Map (Dependencies)
      - **tr**: trigger (s=shallow, d=deep), **md**: maxDepth, **n**: nodes, **e**: edges
    - **sm**: Symbol Map (AST relations)
  - **pf**: Primary File [path, content]
  - **rf**: Related Files [path, reason, mode (f=full, o=outline), content]
  - **s**: Code Snippets [file, line, content]
  - **d**: Diffs (s=staged, u=unstaged, g=git, ut=untracked)
  - **a**: Analysis (ast results)
  - **pm**: Project Metadata (pj=package.json, rh=README header, cf=config files, ai=AI rules)
  - **gh**: Git History (rc=recent commits)
  - **pt**: Project Topology (ms=modules, fs=folder structure)
    - **ms**: name(n), path(p), role(er: c=core, a=adapter, cl=cli, u=util)
  - **kb**: Knowledge Base (pr=rules, ad=decisions, up=user prefs)
    - **ad**: [ [Date, Content, Files[]], ... ] (Positional tuples)
  - **ra**: Runtime Artifacts (bd=build dirs, ev=env vars, lf=lock files)
